In order to run this project you would need java 11 and Gradle 6.9.4

H2 console url- http://localhost:8080/h2-console

Run gradle build command from your terminal and then start your server.

It exposes below endpoints:

upload file:
POST: http://localhost:8080/files

To hit this api from postman, you would need to upload a file. Follow steps below to do that
select body -> form-data - it would ask for key value
file will be the key in value there is a drop down that you need to change from text to file.
once you will do that, it will give you a button to select a file. select the file that you want to upload
and then finally click on the send button.

Get all files:
GET: http://localhost:8080/files

Delete an already uploaded file:
DELETE: http://localhost:8080/files/2 (where 2 is the id of the file that you want to delete.)

Create post:
POST: http://localhost:8080/documents/2/posts

Get Post for give file:
GET: http://localhost:8080/documents/2/posts

Create comment:
POST: http://localhost:8080/documents/1/comments
